Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Yellow Thai Style Chicken Noodles with Bell Pepper and Tenderstem® Broccoli in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen a higher protein version, add the chicken to the pan with the veg, then continue as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Pour the @boiled water{100%ml} for the sauce into a #measuring jug{}.

Pour the remaining @boiled water{for cooking} into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil. Add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @Peanut Butter{30%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Sugar{1.5%tsp} and @boiled water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Stir until well combined.

> TIP: If your peanut butter has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min. Set aside your peanut butter sauce.

Next, cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} into thirds. Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @Carrot{1}, then slice into 0.5cm thick rounds (no need to peel).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g}, broccoli, carrot and sliced pepper and stir-fry until just soft, ~{6-7%minutes}.

While the veg softens, cut the @Lime{1} into wedges. Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

When the veg has softened, lower the heat to medium.

Stir in the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the peanut butter sauce and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles to the pan and toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Squeeze in half the lime juice, then remove from the heat.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed.

Share the yellow Thai style noodles between your #serving bowls{}. Sprinkle over the peanuts.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges to finish. Enjoy!